When a user inputs a question in the frontend, it is sent as a POST request to the FastAPI backend.
The backend receives the user's question and processes it using the langchain library to prepare it
for input to the AI model.
The preprocessed question is then sent as a POST request to the OpenAI API using the openai
library.
The GPT-3.5-turbo model generates a response based on the input question and returns it to the
backend.
The backend receives the AI-generated response and indexes it using the llama-index(trained it
using my resume and few more documents) library for efficient storage and retrieval.
The response is sent back to the frontend, where it is displayed to the user as the answer to their
